sts that multiple mechanisms are responsible for\nUDG formation and that prolonged transformation of cluster dwarfs is not a\nprimary UDG formation mechanism at high-$z$. Furthermore, we find a slight\noverabundance of LDGs in El Gordo, and, in contrast to findings in local\nclusters, our analysis does not show a deficit of LDGs in the center of El\nGordo, implying that tidal destruction of LDGs is significant between $z=0.87$\nand $z=0$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 8 Mar 2023 17:15:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-09"}
