transition and the\nsoft-to-hard transition respectively, which indicates that two classes of\n$\\alpha$ are needed for explaining the hysteresis effect during the state\ntransition. Finally, we argue that such a constrained $\\alpha$ may provide\nvaluable clues for further exploring the accretion physics in BH-XRBs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 9 Mar 2023 03:33:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-29"}
