ripped mass from a non-degenerate companion star\n($\\lesssim0.003\\,M_{\\odot}$ for H$\\alpha$ emission). The early excess light in\nthe multi-band light curve supports a non-degenerate companion in the\nprogenitor system of SN 2021hpr. At the same time, the non-detection of\nemission lines opens a door for other methods to explain this event.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 9 Mar 2023 05:55:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-31"}
